content.description: A relatively simple climb.  Horizontal cracks may offer good hands or may be too thin.  Start with hands just above the second horizontal crack on the left.  Side pull hard as you climb.  Getting over the top is a little tricky.  An undercling approach may be possible but is untested, use best judgement when determining the strength of the rock...
content.protection: Top rope possible.  Landing zone is pretty flat so a few pads for bouldering and a spotter should do.
content.location: Second vertical crack to the right of the raised column on the west facing wall.

content.description: A series of crack-ish climbs on the bridge buttresses.  Landing areas are relatively flat with rocky floor.  Most climbs are covered from rain by the bridge.
